ton, Lancashire, England":"Hoghton, Lancashire, England"},"nl":{"about 1479–about 1503":"circa 1479–circa 1503","1475–Female":"1475–Overleden","1479–1503":"1479–1503","1482–1527":"1482–1527","1496–1559":"1496–1559","1500–1589":"1500–1589","1500–Female":"1500–Overleden","1483–1520":"1483–1520","1500–1562":"1500–1562","1449–1501":"1449–1501","1454–1540":"1454–1540","1483":"1483","Abt 1500":"circa 1500","1482":"1482","1503":"1503","1501":"1501","1589":"1589","1479":"1479","1500":"1500","about 1503":"circa 1503","1454":"1454","1520":"1520","about 1479":"circa 1479","1475":"1475","18 August 1501":"18 augustus 1501","1540":"1540","1562":"1562","1496":"1496","about 1500":"circa 1500","1527":"1527","1449":"1449","1559":"1559","Titchfield, Hampshire, England":"Titchfield, Hampshire, England","Preston, Lancashire, England":"Preston, Lancashire, England","Hoghton, Lancashire, England":"Hoghton, Lancashire, England"},"en":{"about 1479–about 1503":"about 1479–about 1503","1475–Female":"1475–Deceased","1479–1503":"1479–1503","1482–1527":"1482–1527","1496–1559":"1496–1559","1500–1589":"1500–1589","1500–Female":"1500–Deceased","1483–1520":"1483–1520","1500–1562":"1500–1562","1449–1501":"1449–1501","1454–1540":"1454–1540","1483":"1483","Abt 1500":"about 1500","1482":"1482","1503":"1503","1501":"1501","1589":"1589","1479":"1479","1500":"1500","about 1503":"about 1503","1454":"1454","1520":"1520","about 1479":"about 1479","1475":"1475","18 August 1501":"18 August 1501","1540":"1540","1562":"1562","1496":"1496","about 1500":"about 1500","1527":"1527","1449":"1449","1559":"1559","Titchfield, Hampshire, England":"Titchfield, Hampshire, England","Preston, Lancashire, England":"Preston, Lancashire, England","Hoghton, Lancashire, England":"Hoghton, Lancashire, England","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Houghton","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English:","habitational name from any of numerous places called Houghton or Hoghton. Most of the placenames derive from Old English <i>hōh</i> ‘heel, spur of land’ + <i>tūn</i> ‘farmstead, estate’, though some have different etymologies; for example, Little Houghton in Eccles (Lancashire), which derives from Old English <i>halh</i> ‘nook, corner of land’ + <i>tūn</i>, and Houghton in Bigbury (Devon), which may derive from an Old English personal name <i>Huhha</i> + Old English <i>tūn</i>.","variant of   Haughton  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Haughton","meanings":["English: habitational name from Haughton (Cheshire, Lancashire, Northumberland, Shropshire, Staffordshire), or Haughton le Skerne (Durham). The placenames derive from Old English <i>halh</i> ‘nook, corner of land’ + <i>tūn</i> ‘farmstead, estate’. Compare   Houghton  .","Irish: adopted for <b>Ó hEacháin</b> ‘descendant of <i>Eachán</i>’, a pet form of the personal name <i>Eachaidh</i> (see   Hoey  ).","Irish: adopted for <b>Ó hEachtair</b> ‘descendant of <i>Eachtair</i>’, a personal name of uncertain origin. Compare   Hoctor  ."]},{"name":"Howton","meanings":["English (London): variant of   Houghton  ."]},{"name":"Hufton","meanings":["English: habitational name; probably from Stony Houghton in Pleasley (Derbyshire), the name of which derives from Old English <i>hōh</i> ‘heel, spur of land’ + <i>tūn</i> ‘farmstead, estate’. Compare   Houghton  ."]}]},{"name":"Henry","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["A perennially popular given name, of Continental Germanic origin, from <i>haim</i> ‘home’ + <i>rīc</i> ‘power, ruler’. It was an Old French name, adopted by the Normans and introduced by them to Britain. It has been borne by eight kings of England. Not until the 17th century did the form <i>Henry</i> (as opposed to   Harry  ) become the standard vernacular form, mainly under the influence of the Latin form <i>Henricus</i> and French <i>Henri</i>."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Sir Henry Houghton was born about 1479, in Hoghton, Lancashire, England, his father, Sir William Houghton, was 31 and his mother, Mary Southworth, was 26. He married Joan Bridmore about 1500. They were the parents of at least 1 son. He died about 1503, in Titchfield, Hampshire, England, at the age of 26."},"et":{"about 1479–about 1503":"umbes 1479–umbes 1503","1475–Female":"1475–Surnud","1479–1503":"1479–1503","1482–1527":"1482–1527","1496–1559":"1496–1559","1500–1589":"1500–1589","1500–Female":"1500–Surnud","1483–1520":"1483–1520","1500–1562":"1500–1562","1449–1501":"1449–1501","1454–1540":"1454–1540","1483":"1483","Abt 1500":"umbes 1500","1482":"1482","1503":"1503","1501":"1501","1589":"1589","1479":"1479","1500":"1500","about 1503":"umbes 1503","1454":"1454","1520":"1520","about 1479":"umbes 1479","1475":"1475","18 August 1501":"18. august 1501","1540":"1540","1562":"1562","1496":"1496","about 1500":"umbes 1500","1527":"1527","1449":"1449","1559":"1559","Titchfield, Hampshire, England":"Titchfield, Hampshire, England","Preston, Lancashire, England":"Preston, Lancashire, England","Hoghton, Lancashire, England":"Hoghton, Lancashire, England"},"fi":{"about 1479–about 1503":"noin 1479–noin 1503","1475–Female":"1475–Kuollut","1479–1503":"1479–1503","1482–1527":"1482–1527","1496–1559":"1496–1559","1500–1589":"1500–1589","1500–Female":"1500–Kuollut","1483–1520":"1483–1520","1500–1562":"1500–1562","1449–1501":"1449–1501","1454–1540":"1454–1540","1483":"1483","Abt 1500":"noin 1500","1482":"1482","1503":"1503","1501":"1501","1589":"1589","1479":"1479","1500":"1500","about 1503":"noin 1503","1454":"1454","1520":"1520","about 1479":"noin 1479","1475":"1475","18 August 1501":"18. elokuuta 1501","1540":"1540","1562":"1562","1496":"1496","about 1500":"noin 1500","1527":"1527","1449":"1449","1559":"1559","Titchfield, Hampshire, England":"Titchfield, Hampshire, England","Preston, Lancashire, England":"Preston, Lancashire, England","Hoghton, Lancashire, England":"Hoghton, Lancashire, England"},"fr":{"about 